<body >
   

    <div class="px-10 bg-[#F7F4EB] pt-14  pb-34."> 
       
        <div class="flex flex-row  justify-between  items-center">
            <div class="flex xs:flex-row flex-col md:gap-4 gap-2 justify-center xs:items-center items-start">
            <h1 class="font-[Gambetta]  lg:text-[60px] md:text-[40px] xs:text-[30px] text-[28px]  font-semibold ">Wix Engineering</h1>
            <div class=" xs:w-[1.4px] w-[9.5rem] lg:h-[60px] md:h-[50px] xs:h-[40px] h-[1.2px] bg-[#1D1D1D]"></div>
            <p class="font-[Gambetta] italic  lg:text-[30px]/8 md:text-[20px]/6 font-normal ">where code and creativity meet — a visual <br class="sm:inline hidden"> system for people building the web</p>
            </div>
            <div class="flex flex-col  justify-center items-center ">
                <p class="font-[Gambetta] italic lg:text-[24px]/8 md:text-[20px]/6 text-18/4 font-light ">Year:</p>
                <p class="font-[Gambetta]  lg:text-[26px]/8 md:text-[22px]/6 text-[18px]/4 font-semibold ">2026</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class=" w-100% flex flex-col gap-4 font-[Gambetta] regular md:text-[20px] text-[16px] text-justify justify-center items-center md:py-36 py-24">
            <p class="md:w-[38rem]">Wix Engineering represents  the people building the technologies behind Wix products and services. As the organisation evolved and introduced the concept of the xEngineer -  an AI-native engineer with end-to-end ownership and a design-first mindset, their visual identity and digital presence needed  to better reflect this new chapter.</p>
            <p class="md:w-[38rem]">My task was to evolve the existing Wix Engineering brand, keeping core colors, and making sure it aligns with the recognisability and standards of wider Wix ecosystem. I developed a new visual language inspired by code, systems, and modular thinking, redesigning the main website experience, and later adapting the new identity across additional engineering programs. The result is a more cohesive and future oriented brand that better represents the engineers shaping next generation of web development.</p>
        </div>
        <div class=" grid md:grid-cols-2 grid-cols-1 gap-x-10 gap-y-10 pt-14 pb-[4rem]" >
            <img src="../assets/Engineering1.avif" alt="Website Screens">
            <img src="../assets/Engineering2.avif" alt="Website Screens">
            <img src="../assets/Engineering3.avif" alt="Website Screens">
            <img src="../assets/Engineering4.avif" alt="Website Screens">
            <div></div>
            <div class=" felx flex-col ">
                <h2 class=" font-[Gambetta] text-[#1D1D1D] md:text-[34px] text-[26px]  italic pb-3">challenge: <span class=" text-[#1D1D1D40]"> opportunity & my role</span></h2>
                <div class="font-[Gambetta] text-[#1D1D1D] md:text-[20px] text-[16px] font-regular flex flex-col gap-4 text-justify pb-40">
                <p class="lg:w-[80%]">The Wix Engineering visual system had evolved over time, leading to fragmented communication assets and an external website that no longer felt fully consistent. As the organisation expanded with the introduction of the xEngineer mindset, there was a clear need to reconsider how engineering was represented externally and ensure the identity reflected this new direction.</p>
                <p class="lg:w-[80%]">The challenge was to unify the brand into a coherent and scalable system that aligned with Wix standards while supporting the evolving nature of the engineering organisation.</p>
                <p class="lg:w-[80%]">This was one of my first major projects at Wix, where I had full ownership of the visual system, website design, and supporting communication assets. Throughout the process, I was guided by a senior designer whose deep understanding of Wix’s visual language and brand boundaries helped shape key decisions and define how far the system could be pushed while remaining consistent with the broader Wix brand.</p>
            </div>
            </div>
            <img src="../assets/Engineering5.avif" alt="Wix Engineering Colors">
            <video class="test" height="100%" width="auto" loop autoplay > <source src="../assets/Engineering_6.mp4" type="video/mp4"> </video>
            <div class=" felx flex-col ">
                <h2 class=" font-[Gambetta] text-[#1D1D1D] md:text-[34px] text-[26px] italic pb-3"> branding <span class=" text-[#1D1D1D40]"> reasoning & decisions </span></h2>
                <div class="font-[Gambetta] text-[#1D1D1D] md:text-[20px] text-[16px] font-regular flex flex-col gap-4 text-justify pb-40">
                <p class="lg:w-[80%]">The visual language was designed to translate engineering complexity into clear, structured systems, drawing from code, modular thinking, and familiar developer patterns.</p>
                <p class="lg:w-[80%]">A key decision was to use code as the starting point, gradually morphing it into meaningful engineering symbols. This shift reflects the engineering process itself—moving from dense technical inputs to clearer, reusable systems and outcomes.</p>
                <p class="lg:w-[80%]">Initial explorations focused on abstract code-derived shapes, but were later refined through feedback from the engineering guild. The direction moved toward symbols that carry real meaning within the developer community, making the system more grounded, legible, and relevant to its audience.</p>
                <p class="lg:w-[80%]">To maintain flexibility, abstract and experimental elements were retained for educational and early-career programs, allowing the system to scale across different contexts without diluting the core engineering identity.</p>
                <p class="lg:w-[80%]">Color was kept closely aligned with the wider Wix ecosystem, with subtle refinements to improve contrast and strengthen visual hierarchy.</p>
                <p class="lg:w-[80%]">Overall, the system operates as a flexible framework that reflects Wix Engineering’s nature: modular, evolving, and focused on turning complexity into clarity.</p>




            </div>
            </div>
            <div></div>
            <img src="../assets/Engineering7.avif" alt="Wix Enter">
            <img src="../assets/Engineering8.avif" alt="Wix KickstarterX">
        </div>
      
            
                
